Im currently building an app using a stablediffusion workflow in partnership with a big youtuber 🤫 but only calling stablediffusion. I could imagine a future where tao has an api and we switch. But Im also curious about the possibilities within a miner

If you have trained a checkpoint before, then I suppose that would be the "fine-tuning" unless you're on validation side working on the Image Reward models that score the images, which is certainly something that is being worked on. 

This is firstly an Image generation subnet above all else, and animation is not integrated into the reward model as of yet. It could be argued that another subnet would be required for txt2video/image animation; but I am unsure what others on the network think. The time to create a gif differs greatly when compared to image generation, and could likely be accounted for on this subnet, but I am unsure of how such code would be written, and how it would affect the overall systems already in place for distributing incentive on the subnet. 

Also then we need a reward model capable of properly rewarding gifs, and well, that's easier said than done.. As far as API keys go, I believe some participants may someday soon provide API keys to call the image miners, but things are still being ironed out and developed.
The miner utilizes ComfyUi to process images, so I would recommend getting familiar with that interface, as that is where the workflows are derived from.
If miners wish to provide their workflows to the open competition, by all means, be my guest. But it is likely that people scoring high on incentive will not be inclined to share their secrets

Docker has internal and external ports, sounds like you’re running on runpod or vast where this is the case

The py script will correctly fetch your external ip but it will tell people to connect to your ip:7000. Meanwhile docker has bound your 7000 port to a different number like 18409, so when someone connects externally they’re connecting to the wrong port
To fix that you need to ensure that the internal port of docker and the external port match
